INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1,1,'essential-guide-everest-base-camp-trek','Essential Guide to Everest Base Camp Trek','Everything you need to know before embarking on the journey of a lifetime to the base of the world\'s highest mountain.','<h1>The&nbsp;Essential&nbsp;Guide&nbsp;to&nbsp;Everest&nbsp;Base&nbsp;Camp&nbsp;(EBC)&nbsp;Trek:&nbsp;2026&nbsp;Edition</h1><p>Is&nbsp;standing&nbsp;at&nbsp;the&nbsp;foot&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;world’s&nbsp;highest&nbsp;peak&nbsp;on&nbsp;your&nbsp;bucket&nbsp;list?&nbsp;The&nbsp;Everest&nbsp;Base&nbsp;Camp&nbsp;trek&nbsp;is&nbsp;more&nbsp;than&nbsp;just&nbsp;a&nbsp;hike;&nbsp;it’s&nbsp;a&nbsp;high-altitude&nbsp;pilgrimage&nbsp;through&nbsp;the&nbsp;heart&nbsp;of&nbsp;Sherpa&nbsp;culture.</p><p>At&nbsp;<strong>Zeo&nbsp;Tourism</strong>,&nbsp;we’ve&nbsp;refined&nbsp;the&nbsp;EBC&nbsp;experience&nbsp;to&nbsp;ensure&nbsp;you&nbsp;don’t&nbsp;just&nbsp;reach&nbsp;the&nbsp;base&nbsp;camp,&nbsp;but&nbsp;actually&nbsp;enjoy&nbsp;the&nbsp;journey&nbsp;there.&nbsp;Here&nbsp;is&nbsp;everything&nbsp;you&nbsp;need&nbsp;to&nbsp;know&nbsp;before&nbsp;you&nbsp;lace&nbsp;up&nbsp;your&nbsp;boots.</p><h2>EBC&nbsp;Trek:&nbsp;Quick&nbsp;Facts</h2><table style=\"border: 1px solid #000;\"><tbody><tr><td data-row=\"1\"><strong>Feature</strong></td><td data-row=\"1\"><strong>Details</strong></td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"2\"><strong>Max&nbsp;Elevation</strong></td><td data-row=\"2\">5,644m&nbsp;(Kala&nbsp;Patthar)&nbsp;/&nbsp;5,364m&nbsp;(EBC)</td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"3\"><strong>Duration</strong></td><td data-row=\"3\">12–14&nbsp;Days</td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"4\"><strong>Difficulty</strong></td><td data-row=\"4\">Challenging&nbsp;(No&nbsp;technical&nbsp;climbing&nbsp;required)</td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"5\"><strong>Best&nbsp;Months</strong></td><td data-row=\"5\">March–May&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;September–November</td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"6\"><strong>Permits&nbsp;Required</strong></td><td data-row=\"6\">Sagarmatha&nbsp;National&nbsp;Park&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Khumbu&nbsp;Rural&nbsp;Municipality</td></tr></tbody></table><h2>1.&nbsp;The&nbsp;Ideal&nbsp;14-Day&nbsp;Itinerary</h2><p>We&nbsp;recommend&nbsp;a&nbsp;14-day&nbsp;schedule&nbsp;to&nbsp;allow&nbsp;for&nbsp;<strong>essential&nbsp;acclimatization</strong>.&nbsp;Skipping&nbsp;rest&nbsp;days&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;#1&nbsp;reason&nbsp;trekkers&nbsp;fail&nbsp;to&nbsp;reach&nbsp;the&nbsp;base.</p><ul><li><strong>Day&nbsp;1-2:</strong>&nbsp;Arrival&nbsp;in&nbsp;Kathmandu&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Scenic&nbsp;Flight&nbsp;to&nbsp;Lukla&nbsp;(2,860m).&nbsp;Trek&nbsp;to&nbsp;Phakding.</li><li><strong>Day&nbsp;3-4:</strong>&nbsp;Trek&nbsp;to&nbsp;<strong>Namche&nbsp;Bazaar</strong>&nbsp;(3,440m).&nbsp;We&nbsp;spend&nbsp;an&nbsp;extra&nbsp;night&nbsp;here&nbsp;to&nbsp;help&nbsp;your&nbsp;body&nbsp;adjust&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;&quot;thin&nbsp;air.&quot;</li><li><strong>Day&nbsp;5-6:</strong>&nbsp;Moving&nbsp;higher&nbsp;to&nbsp;Tengboche&nbsp;Monastery&nbsp;and&nbsp;Dingboche&nbsp;(4,410m).&nbsp;Second&nbsp;acclimatization&nbsp;day.</li><li><strong>Day&nbsp;7-9:</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;push&nbsp;to&nbsp;Lobuche&nbsp;and&nbsp;finally&nbsp;<strong>Gorak&nbsp;Shep</strong>.&nbsp;This&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;big&nbsp;moment:&nbsp;Trekking&nbsp;to&nbsp;<strong>Everest&nbsp;Base&nbsp;Camp&nbsp;(5,364m)</strong>.</li><li><strong>Day&nbsp;10:</strong>&nbsp;Sunrise&nbsp;hike&nbsp;to&nbsp;<strong>Kala&nbsp;Patthar&nbsp;(5,644m)</strong>&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;best&nbsp;view&nbsp;of&nbsp;Everest’s&nbsp;summit.</li><li><strong>Day&nbsp;11-14:</strong>&nbsp;Descent&nbsp;to&nbsp;Lukla&nbsp;and&nbsp;flight&nbsp;back&nbsp;to&nbsp;Kathmandu.</li></ul><h2>2.&nbsp;Essential&nbsp;Packing&nbsp;List:&nbsp;What&nbsp;We&nbsp;Recommend</h2><p>Packing&nbsp;too&nbsp;much&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;common&nbsp;mistake.&nbsp;Your&nbsp;porter-carried&nbsp;duffel&nbsp;should&nbsp;ideally&nbsp;stay&nbsp;under&nbsp;<strong>12–15kg</strong>.</p><h3><strong>The&nbsp;Layering&nbsp;System</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Base&nbsp;Layer:</strong>&nbsp;Moisture-wicking&nbsp;thermals&nbsp;(Merino&nbsp;wool&nbsp;is&nbsp;our&nbsp;favorite).</li><li><strong>Mid&nbsp;Layer:</strong>&nbsp;A&nbsp;warm&nbsp;fleece&nbsp;or&nbsp;&quot;down&quot;&nbsp;sweater.</li><li><strong>Outer&nbsp;Shell:</strong>&nbsp;Waterproof&nbsp;and&nbsp;windproof&nbsp;jacket&nbsp;(Gore-Tex&nbsp;or&nbsp;similar).</li><li><strong>The&nbsp;Big&nbsp;Down:</strong>&nbsp;A&nbsp;heavy-duty&nbsp;down&nbsp;jacket&nbsp;rated&nbsp;for&nbsp;-15°C&nbsp;(Essential&nbsp;for&nbsp;evenings).</li></ul><h3><strong>Footwear</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Trekking&nbsp;Boots:</strong>&nbsp;Waterproof&nbsp;with&nbsp;solid&nbsp;ankle&nbsp;support.&nbsp;<strong>Pro&nbsp;Tip:</strong>&nbsp;Break&nbsp;them&nbsp;in&nbsp;at&nbsp;least&nbsp;2&nbsp;months&nbsp;before&nbsp;your&nbsp;flight!</li><li><strong>Camp&nbsp;Shoes:</strong>&nbsp;Lightweight&nbsp;sneakers&nbsp;or&nbsp;Crocs&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;tea&nbsp;houses.</li></ul><h2>3.&nbsp;Health&nbsp;and&nbsp;Safety:&nbsp;Beating&nbsp;AMS</h2><p>Altitude&nbsp;Sickness&nbsp;(AMS)&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;real&nbsp;factor&nbsp;above&nbsp;3,000&nbsp;meters.&nbsp;Here&nbsp;is&nbsp;how&nbsp;we&nbsp;keep&nbsp;our&nbsp;guests&nbsp;safe:</p><ul><li><strong>Hydration:</strong>&nbsp;We&nbsp;insist&nbsp;on&nbsp;drinking&nbsp;3–4&nbsp;liters&nbsp;of&nbsp;water&nbsp;daily.</li><li><strong>Pacing:</strong>&nbsp;&quot;Bistari,&nbsp;bistari&quot;&nbsp;(Slowly,&nbsp;slowly).&nbsp;This&nbsp;isn&#39;t&nbsp;a&nbsp;race.</li><li><strong>Medication:</strong>&nbsp;Consult&nbsp;your&nbsp;doctor&nbsp;about&nbsp;<strong>Diamox</strong>.&nbsp;We&nbsp;always&nbsp;carry&nbsp;oxygen&nbsp;cylinders&nbsp;and&nbsp;oximeters&nbsp;for&nbsp;daily&nbsp;check-ups.</li></ul><h2>ZEO&nbsp;FAQ:&nbsp;Common&nbsp;Search&nbsp;Queries</h2><h3><strong>How&nbsp;much&nbsp;does&nbsp;the&nbsp;Everest&nbsp;Base&nbsp;Camp&nbsp;trek&nbsp;cost?</strong></h3><p>A&nbsp;standard&nbsp;14-day&nbsp;trek&nbsp;usually&nbsp;ranges&nbsp;from&nbsp;<strong>$1,300&nbsp;to&nbsp;$1,800&nbsp;USD</strong>.&nbsp;This&nbsp;includes&nbsp;permits,&nbsp;guides,&nbsp;porters,&nbsp;accommodation,&nbsp;and&nbsp;meals.&nbsp;Luxury&nbsp;&quot;Heli-return&quot;&nbsp;treks&nbsp;can&nbsp;go&nbsp;up&nbsp;to&nbsp;$3,500+.</p><h3><strong>Do&nbsp;I&nbsp;need&nbsp;a&nbsp;guide&nbsp;for&nbsp;EBC&nbsp;in&nbsp;2026?</strong></h3><p>While&nbsp;rules&nbsp;in&nbsp;Nepal&nbsp;have&nbsp;shifted&nbsp;toward&nbsp;mandatory&nbsp;guides&nbsp;for&nbsp;many&nbsp;regions,&nbsp;the&nbsp;Khumbu&nbsp;region&nbsp;(Everest)&nbsp;still&nbsp;allows&nbsp;solo&nbsp;trekking&nbsp;in&nbsp;some&nbsp;areas.&nbsp;However,&nbsp;we&nbsp;strongly&nbsp;advise&nbsp;a&nbsp;licensed&nbsp;guide&nbsp;for&nbsp;safety,&nbsp;navigation,&nbsp;and&nbsp;deeper&nbsp;cultural&nbsp;insight.</p><h3><strong>Is&nbsp;there&nbsp;Wi-Fi&nbsp;and&nbsp;electricity&nbsp;on&nbsp;the&nbsp;trail?</strong></h3><p>Yes.&nbsp;Most&nbsp;tea&nbsp;houses&nbsp;offer&nbsp;Wi-Fi&nbsp;(via&nbsp;AirLink&nbsp;cards)&nbsp;and&nbsp;charging&nbsp;stations&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;small&nbsp;fee&nbsp;(approx.&nbsp;$3–$5&nbsp;per&nbsp;charge).&nbsp;We&nbsp;suggest&nbsp;bringing&nbsp;a&nbsp;high-capacity&nbsp;power&nbsp;bank.</p><h2>Why&nbsp;Trek&nbsp;with&nbsp;Zeo&nbsp;Tourism?</h2><p>We&nbsp;don&#39;t&nbsp;just&nbsp;book&nbsp;hotels;&nbsp;we&nbsp;curate&nbsp;experiences.&nbsp;From&nbsp;ensuring&nbsp;you&nbsp;get&nbsp;the&nbsp;best&nbsp;&quot;mountain-view&quot;&nbsp;rooms&nbsp;in&nbsp;Namche&nbsp;to&nbsp;providing&nbsp;locally&nbsp;sourced,&nbsp;high-energy&nbsp;meals,&nbsp;we&nbsp;handle&nbsp;the&nbsp;details&nbsp;so&nbsp;you&nbsp;can&nbsp;focus&nbsp;on&nbsp;the&nbsp;mountains.</p>','https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1522163182402-834f871fd851?q=80&w=2070','Pemba Sherpa','Trekking Tips',NULL,'8 min read',1,'published',NULL,'2024-03-14 18:15:00','2026-07-05 19:18:59','2025-12-20 13:17:42'),(2,2,'sacred-journey-kailash-mansarovar','Sacred Journey: Understanding Kailash Mansarovar','Discover the spiritual significance and practical aspects of this holy pilgrimage that attracts thousands each year.','<p>For&nbsp;centuries,&nbsp;the&nbsp;call&nbsp;of&nbsp;<strong>Mount&nbsp;Kailash</strong>&nbsp;has&nbsp;echoed&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;hearts&nbsp;of&nbsp;seekers,&nbsp;pilgrims,&nbsp;and&nbsp;adventurers&nbsp;alike.&nbsp;It&nbsp;is&nbsp;not&nbsp;just&nbsp;a&nbsp;destination;&nbsp;it&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;transition&nbsp;from&nbsp;the&nbsp;material&nbsp;world&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;metaphysical.&nbsp;As&nbsp;we&nbsp;look&nbsp;toward&nbsp;the&nbsp;2025-2026&nbsp;season,&nbsp;we&nbsp;invite&nbsp;you&nbsp;to&nbsp;understand&nbsp;what&nbsp;makes&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>Kailash&nbsp;Mansarovar&nbsp;Yatra</strong>&nbsp;the&nbsp;most&nbsp;significant&nbsp;spiritual&nbsp;odyssey&nbsp;on&nbsp;Earth.</p><h2>The&nbsp;Spiritual&nbsp;Heart&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;World</h2><p>Mount&nbsp;Kailash,&nbsp;standing&nbsp;at&nbsp;<strong>6,638&nbsp;meters</strong>,&nbsp;is&nbsp;more&nbsp;than&nbsp;a&nbsp;mountain—it&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;<em>Axis&nbsp;Mundi</em>,&nbsp;the&nbsp;cosmic&nbsp;center&nbsp;where&nbsp;heaven&nbsp;meets&nbsp;earth.</p><ul><li><strong>For&nbsp;Hindus:</strong>&nbsp;It&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;eternal&nbsp;abode&nbsp;of&nbsp;Lord&nbsp;Shiva&nbsp;and&nbsp;Goddess&nbsp;Parvati.</li><li><strong>For&nbsp;Buddhists:</strong>&nbsp;It&nbsp;is&nbsp;<em>Kang&nbsp;Rinpoche</em>,&nbsp;representing&nbsp;the&nbsp;mind&nbsp;of&nbsp;Buddha&nbsp;and&nbsp;supreme&nbsp;bliss.</li><li><strong>For&nbsp;Jains:</strong>&nbsp;It&nbsp;is&nbsp;<em>Ashtapada</em>,&nbsp;the&nbsp;site&nbsp;where&nbsp;the&nbsp;first&nbsp;Tirthankara,&nbsp;Rishabhadeva,&nbsp;attained&nbsp;liberation.</li><li><strong>For&nbsp;Bonpos:</strong>&nbsp;It&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;seat&nbsp;of&nbsp;all&nbsp;spiritual&nbsp;power.</li></ul><p>Adjacent&nbsp;to&nbsp;this&nbsp;majestic&nbsp;peak&nbsp;lies&nbsp;<strong>Lake&nbsp;Mansarovar</strong>,&nbsp;the&nbsp;highest&nbsp;freshwater&nbsp;lake&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;world.&nbsp;We&nbsp;believe&nbsp;that&nbsp;a&nbsp;dip&nbsp;in&nbsp;its&nbsp;pristine,&nbsp;sapphire-blue&nbsp;waters&nbsp;(now&nbsp;traditionally&nbsp;performed&nbsp;via&nbsp;bucket&nbsp;bathing&nbsp;to&nbsp;preserve&nbsp;the&nbsp;lake’s&nbsp;sanctity)&nbsp;purifies&nbsp;the&nbsp;soul&nbsp;of&nbsp;lifetimes&nbsp;of&nbsp;karmic&nbsp;debt.</p><p></p><h2>Choosing&nbsp;Your&nbsp;Path:&nbsp;The&nbsp;Routes&nbsp;via&nbsp;Nepal</h2><p>Navigating&nbsp;the&nbsp;high-altitude&nbsp;terrain&nbsp;of&nbsp;Tibet&nbsp;requires&nbsp;careful&nbsp;planning.&nbsp;We&nbsp;typically&nbsp;offer&nbsp;three&nbsp;primary&nbsp;ways&nbsp;to&nbsp;reach&nbsp;the&nbsp;sacred&nbsp;site:</p><h3>1.&nbsp;The&nbsp;Overland&nbsp;Route&nbsp;(Kerung&nbsp;Border)</h3><p>This&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;classic,&nbsp;most&nbsp;scenic&nbsp;journey.&nbsp;We&nbsp;drive&nbsp;from&nbsp;<strong>Kathmandu</strong>&nbsp;through&nbsp;the&nbsp;lush&nbsp;greenery&nbsp;of&nbsp;Nepal,&nbsp;crossing&nbsp;into&nbsp;Tibet&nbsp;via&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>Kerung&nbsp;Border</strong>.&nbsp;It&nbsp;allows&nbsp;for&nbsp;gradual&nbsp;acclimatization&nbsp;as&nbsp;we&nbsp;traverse&nbsp;the&nbsp;vast&nbsp;Tibetan&nbsp;Plateau.</p><h3>2.&nbsp;The&nbsp;Helicopter&nbsp;Route&nbsp;(Simikot/Hilsa)</h3><p>For&nbsp;those&nbsp;with&nbsp;limited&nbsp;time&nbsp;or&nbsp;seeking&nbsp;more&nbsp;comfort,&nbsp;we&nbsp;fly&nbsp;from&nbsp;<strong>Nepalgunj&nbsp;to&nbsp;Simikot</strong>,&nbsp;then&nbsp;take&nbsp;a&nbsp;helicopter&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>Hilsa&nbsp;border</strong>.&nbsp;This&nbsp;route&nbsp;bypasses&nbsp;long&nbsp;drives&nbsp;and&nbsp;offers&nbsp;breathtaking&nbsp;aerial&nbsp;views&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;Himalayas.</p><h3>3.&nbsp;The&nbsp;Lhasa&nbsp;Route&nbsp;(Flight&nbsp;via&nbsp;Kathmandu)</h3><p>If&nbsp;you&nbsp;wish&nbsp;to&nbsp;blend&nbsp;spirituality&nbsp;with&nbsp;Tibetan&nbsp;culture,&nbsp;this&nbsp;route&nbsp;flies&nbsp;you&nbsp;directly&nbsp;into&nbsp;<strong>Lhasa</strong>.&nbsp;We&nbsp;spend&nbsp;time&nbsp;exploring&nbsp;the&nbsp;Potala&nbsp;Palace&nbsp;and&nbsp;Jokhang&nbsp;Temple&nbsp;before&nbsp;heading&nbsp;west&nbsp;toward&nbsp;Mount&nbsp;Kailash.</p><h2>The&nbsp;Ultimate&nbsp;Challenge:&nbsp;The&nbsp;Kailash&nbsp;Parikrama</h2><p>The&nbsp;centerpiece&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;journey&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>Kora</strong>&nbsp;(circumambulation)&nbsp;around&nbsp;Mount&nbsp;Kailash.&nbsp;This&nbsp;52km&nbsp;trek&nbsp;is&nbsp;physically&nbsp;demanding&nbsp;but&nbsp;spiritually&nbsp;rewarding.</p><ul><li><strong>Yam&nbsp;Dwar:</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;&quot;Gateway&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;God&nbsp;of&nbsp;Death,&quot;&nbsp;where&nbsp;we&nbsp;leave&nbsp;our&nbsp;worldly&nbsp;ego&nbsp;behind&nbsp;to&nbsp;begin&nbsp;the&nbsp;trek.</li><li><strong>Dolma&nbsp;La&nbsp;Pass&nbsp;(5,636m):</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;highest&nbsp;and&nbsp;toughest&nbsp;point&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;journey.&nbsp;Crossing&nbsp;this&nbsp;pass&nbsp;symbolizes&nbsp;a&nbsp;spiritual&nbsp;rebirth.</li><li><strong>Gauri&nbsp;Kunda:</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;&quot;Lake&nbsp;of&nbsp;Compassion,&quot;&nbsp;located&nbsp;just&nbsp;below&nbsp;the&nbsp;pass,&nbsp;where&nbsp;many&nbsp;pilgrims&nbsp;offer&nbsp;prayers.</li></ul><h2>Essential&nbsp;Preparation&nbsp;for&nbsp;2025/2026</h2><p>We&nbsp;want&nbsp;your&nbsp;journey&nbsp;to&nbsp;be&nbsp;as&nbsp;safe&nbsp;as&nbsp;it&nbsp;is&nbsp;sacred.&nbsp;Here&nbsp;is&nbsp;what&nbsp;you&nbsp;need&nbsp;to&nbsp;know:</p><ul><li><strong>Permits&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Visas:</strong>&nbsp;You&nbsp;cannot&nbsp;travel&nbsp;to&nbsp;Tibet&nbsp;independently.&nbsp;We&nbsp;handle&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>Tibet&nbsp;Travel&nbsp;Permit&nbsp;(TTP)</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>Chinese&nbsp;Group&nbsp;Visa</strong>&nbsp;through&nbsp;our&nbsp;authorized&nbsp;channels&nbsp;in&nbsp;Kathmandu.</li><li><strong>Physical&nbsp;Fitness:</strong>&nbsp;Start&nbsp;your&nbsp;preparation&nbsp;3-4&nbsp;months&nbsp;in&nbsp;advance.&nbsp;We&nbsp;recommend&nbsp;cardiovascular&nbsp;exercises,&nbsp;yoga,&nbsp;and&nbsp;breathing&nbsp;techniques&nbsp;(Pranayama)&nbsp;to&nbsp;help&nbsp;your&nbsp;body&nbsp;cope&nbsp;with&nbsp;low&nbsp;oxygen&nbsp;levels.</li><li><strong>Health&nbsp;Checks:</strong>&nbsp;A&nbsp;recent&nbsp;medical&nbsp;fitness&nbsp;certificate&nbsp;is&nbsp;mandatory.&nbsp;We&nbsp;monitor&nbsp;oxygen&nbsp;levels&nbsp;daily&nbsp;during&nbsp;the&nbsp;trip&nbsp;to&nbsp;ensure&nbsp;everyone’s&nbsp;safety.</li><li><strong>Packing&nbsp;Essentials:</strong>&nbsp;Think&nbsp;layers!&nbsp;You’ll&nbsp;need&nbsp;thermal&nbsp;wear,&nbsp;windproof&nbsp;jackets,&nbsp;sturdy&nbsp;trekking&nbsp;boots,&nbsp;and&nbsp;polarized&nbsp;sunglasses&nbsp;to&nbsp;protect&nbsp;against&nbsp;the&nbsp;intense&nbsp;high-altitude&nbsp;sun.</li></ul><h2>Why&nbsp;Journey&nbsp;With&nbsp;Us?</h2><p>At&nbsp;<strong>Zeotourism</strong>,&nbsp;we&nbsp;understand&nbsp;that&nbsp;this&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;once-in-a-lifetime&nbsp;calling.&nbsp;We&nbsp;don&#39;t&nbsp;just&nbsp;provide&nbsp;transport;&nbsp;we&nbsp;facilitate&nbsp;an&nbsp;experience.&nbsp;From&nbsp;ensuring&nbsp;high-quality&nbsp;vegetarian&nbsp;meals&nbsp;to&nbsp;providing&nbsp;experienced&nbsp;Sherpa&nbsp;support&nbsp;and&nbsp;oxygen&nbsp;backup,&nbsp;we&nbsp;manage&nbsp;the&nbsp;logistics&nbsp;so&nbsp;you&nbsp;can&nbsp;focus&nbsp;on&nbsp;your&nbsp;inner&nbsp;journey.</p><blockquote>&quot;The&nbsp;pilgrimage&nbsp;to&nbsp;Kailash&nbsp;is&nbsp;not&nbsp;about&nbsp;reaching&nbsp;the&nbsp;top&nbsp;of&nbsp;a&nbsp;mountain,&nbsp;but&nbsp;about&nbsp;reaching&nbsp;the&nbsp;depth&nbsp;of&nbsp;your&nbsp;own&nbsp;soul.&quot;</blockquote><h3><strong>Ready&nbsp;to&nbsp;answer&nbsp;the&nbsp;call?</strong></h3><h1>Join&nbsp;us&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>Kailash&nbsp;Mansarovar&nbsp;Yatra&nbsp;2025</strong>.&nbsp;Space&nbsp;is&nbsp;limited&nbsp;due&nbsp;to&nbsp;strict&nbsp;permit&nbsp;quotas,&nbsp;so&nbsp;we&nbsp;encourage&nbsp;early&nbsp;registration&nbsp;to&nbsp;secure&nbsp;your&nbsp;spiritual&nbsp;passage.</h1>','https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1627894483216-2138af692e32?q=80&w=2070','Tenzin Norbu','Spiritual Journeys',NULL,'6 min read',1,'published',NULL,'2024-03-09 18:15:00','2026-07-05 19:19:00','2025-12-20 13:24:14'),(3,3,'best-time-visit-nepal-seasonal-guide','Best Time to Visit Nepal: A Seasonal Guide','From clear mountain views to vibrant festivals, learn when to plan your Nepal adventure for the best experience.','<h2>At&nbsp;a&nbsp;Glance:&nbsp;Nepal&nbsp;Travel&nbsp;Seasons</h2><p>If&nbsp;you’re&nbsp;looking&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;quick&nbsp;answer,&nbsp;here&nbsp;is&nbsp;how&nbsp;we&nbsp;categorize&nbsp;the&nbsp;trekking&nbsp;and&nbsp;touring&nbsp;calendar:</p><table style=\"border: 1px solid #000;\"><tbody><tr><td data-row=\"1\"><strong>Season</strong></td><td data-row=\"1\"><strong>Months</strong></td><td data-row=\"1\"><strong>Best&nbsp;For</strong></td><td data-row=\"1\"><strong>Visibility&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Weather</strong></td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"2\"><strong>Peak&nbsp;(Spring)</strong></td><td data-row=\"2\">March&nbsp;–&nbsp;May</td><td data-row=\"2\">Everest/Annapurna&nbsp;Trekking</td><td data-row=\"2\">Crystal&nbsp;clear,&nbsp;Rhododendrons&nbsp;in&nbsp;bloom</td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"3\"><strong>Low&nbsp;(Monsoon)</strong></td><td data-row=\"3\">June&nbsp;–&nbsp;August</td><td data-row=\"3\">Mustang/Dolpo&nbsp;(Rain&nbsp;Shadow)</td><td data-row=\"3\">Lush&nbsp;greenery,&nbsp;fewer&nbsp;tourists,&nbsp;rain</td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"4\"><strong>Peak&nbsp;(Autumn)</strong></td><td data-row=\"4\">Sept&nbsp;–&nbsp;Nov</td><td data-row=\"4\">Peak&nbsp;Climbing&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Festivals</td><td data-row=\"4\">Best&nbsp;visibility,&nbsp;crisp&nbsp;air,&nbsp;Dashain/Tihar</td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"5\"><strong>Off-Peak&nbsp;(Winter)</strong></td><td data-row=\"5\">Dec&nbsp;–&nbsp;Feb</td><td data-row=\"5\">Jungle&nbsp;Safaris&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Lowland&nbsp;Tours</td><td data-row=\"5\">Sunny&nbsp;days,&nbsp;cold&nbsp;nights,&nbsp;quiet&nbsp;trails</td></tr></tbody></table><h2>1.&nbsp;Spring&nbsp;(March&nbsp;to&nbsp;May):&nbsp;The&nbsp;Season&nbsp;of&nbsp;Flowers</h2><p><strong>Best&nbsp;for:</strong>&nbsp;High-altitude&nbsp;trekking&nbsp;and&nbsp;wildlife&nbsp;spotting.</p><p>We&nbsp;consider&nbsp;Spring&nbsp;the&nbsp;second-best&nbsp;time&nbsp;for&nbsp;trekking,&nbsp;but&nbsp;the&nbsp;absolute&nbsp;best&nbsp;for&nbsp;nature&nbsp;lovers.&nbsp;As&nbsp;the&nbsp;snow&nbsp;melts,&nbsp;the&nbsp;trails&nbsp;to&nbsp;<strong>Annapurna</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Everest</strong>&nbsp;become&nbsp;vibrant&nbsp;with&nbsp;red&nbsp;and&nbsp;pink&nbsp;rhododendrons.</p><ul><li><strong>Why&nbsp;we&nbsp;love&nbsp;it:</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;temperatures&nbsp;are&nbsp;moderate,&nbsp;making&nbsp;long&nbsp;trekking&nbsp;days&nbsp;comfortable.</li><li><strong>Pro&nbsp;Tip:</strong>&nbsp;If&nbsp;you’re&nbsp;visiting&nbsp;<strong>Chitwan&nbsp;National&nbsp;Park</strong>,&nbsp;this&nbsp;is&nbsp;when&nbsp;the&nbsp;tall&nbsp;grass&nbsp;is&nbsp;cut,&nbsp;making&nbsp;it&nbsp;much&nbsp;easier&nbsp;to&nbsp;spot&nbsp;tigers&nbsp;and&nbsp;rhinos.</li></ul><h2>2.&nbsp;Autumn&nbsp;(September&nbsp;to&nbsp;November):&nbsp;The&nbsp;Gold&nbsp;Standard</h2><p><strong>Best&nbsp;for:</strong>&nbsp;Clear&nbsp;mountain&nbsp;views&nbsp;and&nbsp;cultural&nbsp;immersion.</p><p>This&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;most&nbsp;popular&nbsp;time&nbsp;to&nbsp;visit&nbsp;Nepal.&nbsp;After&nbsp;the&nbsp;monsoon&nbsp;rains&nbsp;wash&nbsp;away&nbsp;the&nbsp;dust,&nbsp;the&nbsp;atmosphere&nbsp;is&nbsp;at&nbsp;its&nbsp;clearest.</p><ul><li><strong>The&nbsp;View:</strong>&nbsp;You&nbsp;get&nbsp;those&nbsp;&quot;postcard-perfect&quot;&nbsp;views&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;Himalayas&nbsp;from&nbsp;everywhere—Nagarkot,&nbsp;Sarangkot,&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;high&nbsp;passes.</li><li><strong>Festivals:</strong>&nbsp;We&nbsp;highly&nbsp;recommend&nbsp;visiting&nbsp;during&nbsp;<strong>Dashain&nbsp;and&nbsp;Tihar</strong>&nbsp;(October/November).&nbsp;The&nbsp;energy&nbsp;in&nbsp;Kathmandu&nbsp;is&nbsp;electric,&nbsp;and&nbsp;you’ll&nbsp;experience&nbsp;the&nbsp;true&nbsp;heart&nbsp;of&nbsp;Nepali&nbsp;hospitality.</li></ul><h2>3.&nbsp;Winter&nbsp;(December&nbsp;to&nbsp;February):&nbsp;The&nbsp;Peaceful&nbsp;Choice</h2><p><strong>Best&nbsp;for:</strong>&nbsp;Photography&nbsp;and&nbsp;budget-friendly&nbsp;cultural&nbsp;tours.</p><p>While&nbsp;the&nbsp;high-altitude&nbsp;passes&nbsp;may&nbsp;be&nbsp;blocked&nbsp;by&nbsp;snow,&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>Kathmandu&nbsp;Valley</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Lumbini</strong>,&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Pokhara</strong>&nbsp;remain&nbsp;pleasantly&nbsp;sunny&nbsp;during&nbsp;the&nbsp;day.</p><ul><li><strong>The&nbsp;Perk:</strong>&nbsp;Trails&nbsp;are&nbsp;empty.&nbsp;If&nbsp;you&nbsp;don’t&nbsp;mind&nbsp;the&nbsp;cold&nbsp;(night&nbsp;temps&nbsp;can&nbsp;drop&nbsp;below&nbsp;freezing),&nbsp;you’ll&nbsp;have&nbsp;the&nbsp;mountains&nbsp;all&nbsp;to&nbsp;yourself.</li><li><strong>Zeo’s&nbsp;Pick:</strong>&nbsp;Try&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>Ghorepani&nbsp;Poon&nbsp;Hill</strong>&nbsp;trek&nbsp;in&nbsp;winter&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;stunning&nbsp;sunrise&nbsp;without&nbsp;the&nbsp;crowds.</li></ul><h2>4.&nbsp;Summer/Monsoon&nbsp;(June&nbsp;to&nbsp;August):&nbsp;The&nbsp;Off-Beat&nbsp;Adventure</h2><p><strong>Best&nbsp;for:</strong>&nbsp;Trans-Himalayan&nbsp;treks&nbsp;and&nbsp;lush&nbsp;landscapes.</p><p>Most&nbsp;people&nbsp;avoid&nbsp;the&nbsp;monsoon,&nbsp;but&nbsp;we&nbsp;believe&nbsp;it’s&nbsp;Nepal’s&nbsp;best-kept&nbsp;secret&nbsp;for&nbsp;specific&nbsp;regions.</p><ul><li><strong>Rain&nbsp;Shadow&nbsp;Areas:</strong>&nbsp;Places&nbsp;like&nbsp;<strong>Upper&nbsp;Mustang</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Upper&nbsp;Dolpo</strong>&nbsp;sit&nbsp;behind&nbsp;the&nbsp;mountains,&nbsp;meaning&nbsp;they&nbsp;stay&nbsp;dry&nbsp;while&nbsp;the&nbsp;rest&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;country&nbsp;is&nbsp;rainy.</li><li><strong>Lush&nbsp;Scenery:</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;hills&nbsp;turn&nbsp;an&nbsp;incredible&nbsp;shade&nbsp;of&nbsp;emerald&nbsp;green,&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;waterfalls&nbsp;are&nbsp;at&nbsp;their&nbsp;most&nbsp;powerful.</li></ul><h2>Frequently&nbsp;Asked&nbsp;Questions&nbsp;(ZEO&nbsp;Focus)</h2><h3><strong>What&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;cheapest&nbsp;month&nbsp;to&nbsp;fly&nbsp;to&nbsp;Nepal?</strong></h3><p>Typically,&nbsp;the&nbsp;monsoon&nbsp;months&nbsp;(<strong>June&nbsp;to&nbsp;August</strong>)&nbsp;and&nbsp;late&nbsp;winter&nbsp;(<strong>January</strong>)&nbsp;offer&nbsp;the&nbsp;lowest&nbsp;airfares&nbsp;and&nbsp;hotel&nbsp;rates.&nbsp;We&nbsp;can&nbsp;help&nbsp;you&nbsp;find&nbsp;&quot;off-season&quot;&nbsp;luxury&nbsp;stays&nbsp;at&nbsp;a&nbsp;fraction&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;price.</p><h3><strong>When&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;best&nbsp;time&nbsp;for&nbsp;an&nbsp;Everest&nbsp;Base&nbsp;Camp&nbsp;trek?</strong></h3><p>The&nbsp;&quot;window&quot;&nbsp;is&nbsp;usually&nbsp;<strong>late&nbsp;April&nbsp;to&nbsp;mid-May</strong>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<strong>October&nbsp;to&nbsp;November</strong>.&nbsp;These&nbsp;months&nbsp;offer&nbsp;the&nbsp;safest&nbsp;conditions&nbsp;and&nbsp;best&nbsp;visibility&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;world’s&nbsp;highest&nbsp;peak.</p><h3><strong>Is&nbsp;Nepal&nbsp;safe&nbsp;to&nbsp;visit&nbsp;during&nbsp;the&nbsp;monsoon?</strong></h3><p>Yes,&nbsp;but&nbsp;travel&nbsp;requires&nbsp;flexibility.&nbsp;While&nbsp;flights&nbsp;to&nbsp;Lukla&nbsp;may&nbsp;be&nbsp;delayed&nbsp;due&nbsp;to&nbsp;clouds,&nbsp;road&nbsp;trips&nbsp;through&nbsp;the&nbsp;valley&nbsp;and&nbsp;cultural&nbsp;tours&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;cities&nbsp;are&nbsp;perfectly&nbsp;fine.</p><h2>Start&nbsp;Your&nbsp;Journey&nbsp;with&nbsp;Zeo&nbsp;Tourism</h2><p>Choosing&nbsp;the&nbsp;right&nbsp;season&nbsp;depends&nbsp;on&nbsp;what&nbsp;you&nbsp;want&nbsp;to&nbsp;experience.&nbsp;Whether&nbsp;it&#39;s&nbsp;a&nbsp;high-altitude&nbsp;adrenaline&nbsp;rush&nbsp;or&nbsp;a&nbsp;spiritual&nbsp;journey&nbsp;through&nbsp;ancient&nbsp;temples,&nbsp;we&nbsp;handle&nbsp;the&nbsp;logistics&nbsp;so&nbsp;you&nbsp;can&nbsp;focus&nbsp;on&nbsp;the&nbsp;views.</p>','https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1544735716-392fe2489ffa?q=80&w=2070','Maya Gurung','Travel Planning',NULL,'5 min read',1,'published',NULL,'2024-03-04 18:15:00','2026-07-05 19:19:00','2025-12-20 13:23:40'),(4,4,'altitude-sickness-prevention-management','Altitude Sickness: Prevention and Management','Expert advice on recognizing, preventing, and dealing with altitude sickness during high-altitude treks.','<h1>Altitude&nbsp;Sickness:&nbsp;The&nbsp;Ultimate&nbsp;Prevention&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Management&nbsp;Guide</h1><p>Scaling&nbsp;the&nbsp;Himalayas&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;dream&nbsp;for&nbsp;many,&nbsp;but&nbsp;the&nbsp;&quot;thin&nbsp;air&quot;&nbsp;above&nbsp;3,000&nbsp;meters&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;formidable&nbsp;challenge.&nbsp;At&nbsp;<strong>Zeo&nbsp;Tourism</strong>,&nbsp;your&nbsp;safety&nbsp;is&nbsp;our&nbsp;baseline.&nbsp;Understanding&nbsp;Altitude&nbsp;Sickness—or&nbsp;Acute&nbsp;Mountain&nbsp;Sickness&nbsp;(AMS)—is&nbsp;the&nbsp;difference&nbsp;between&nbsp;reaching&nbsp;the&nbsp;summit&nbsp;and&nbsp;a&nbsp;forced&nbsp;helicopter&nbsp;evacuation.</p><p>Here&nbsp;is&nbsp;our&nbsp;expert&nbsp;manual&nbsp;on&nbsp;how&nbsp;we&nbsp;help&nbsp;you&nbsp;prevent,&nbsp;identify,&nbsp;and&nbsp;manage&nbsp;altitude&nbsp;sickness&nbsp;during&nbsp;your&nbsp;Nepal&nbsp;trek.</p><h2>1.&nbsp;Understanding&nbsp;the&nbsp;Spectrum&nbsp;of&nbsp;Altitude&nbsp;Illness</h2><p>Altitude&nbsp;sickness&nbsp;isn&#39;t&nbsp;a&nbsp;single&nbsp;condition;&nbsp;it&nbsp;exists&nbsp;on&nbsp;a&nbsp;spectrum.&nbsp;We&nbsp;train&nbsp;our&nbsp;guides&nbsp;to&nbsp;monitor&nbsp;for&nbsp;three&nbsp;specific&nbsp;types:</p><ul><li><strong>AMS&nbsp;(Acute&nbsp;Mountain&nbsp;Sickness):</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;most&nbsp;common&nbsp;form.&nbsp;It&nbsp;feels&nbsp;like&nbsp;a&nbsp;bad&nbsp;hangover&nbsp;(headache,&nbsp;nausea,&nbsp;fatigue).</li><li><strong>HAPE&nbsp;(High&nbsp;Altitude&nbsp;Pulmonary&nbsp;Edema):</strong>&nbsp;Fluid&nbsp;buildup&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;lungs.&nbsp;Signs&nbsp;include&nbsp;a&nbsp;persistent&nbsp;cough&nbsp;and&nbsp;extreme&nbsp;breathlessness&nbsp;even&nbsp;while&nbsp;resting.</li><li><strong>HACE&nbsp;(High&nbsp;Altitude&nbsp;Cerebral&nbsp;Edema):</strong>&nbsp;Fluid&nbsp;buildup&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;brain.&nbsp;This&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;medical&nbsp;emergency&nbsp;marked&nbsp;by&nbsp;confusion&nbsp;and&nbsp;a&nbsp;&quot;drunken&nbsp;gait&quot;&nbsp;(ataxia).</li></ul><h2>2.&nbsp;Our&nbsp;&quot;Golden&nbsp;Rules&quot;&nbsp;for&nbsp;Prevention</h2><p>We&nbsp;don&#39;t&nbsp;leave&nbsp;acclimatization&nbsp;to&nbsp;chance.&nbsp;We&nbsp;build&nbsp;every&nbsp;itinerary&nbsp;around&nbsp;these&nbsp;non-negotiable&nbsp;rules:</p><h3><strong>The&nbsp;500m&nbsp;Rule</strong></h3><p>Once&nbsp;we&nbsp;pass&nbsp;3,000m&nbsp;(9,842ft),&nbsp;we&nbsp;ensure&nbsp;your&nbsp;sleeping&nbsp;altitude&nbsp;does&nbsp;not&nbsp;increase&nbsp;by&nbsp;more&nbsp;than&nbsp;<strong>300–500&nbsp;meters&nbsp;per&nbsp;day</strong>.&nbsp;Every&nbsp;1,000m&nbsp;of&nbsp;gain,&nbsp;we&nbsp;schedule&nbsp;a&nbsp;mandatory&nbsp;acclimatization&nbsp;day.</p><h3><strong>Climb&nbsp;High,&nbsp;Sleep&nbsp;Low</strong></h3><p>This&nbsp;is&nbsp;our&nbsp;favorite&nbsp;strategy.&nbsp;During&nbsp;&quot;rest&nbsp;days&quot;&nbsp;in&nbsp;Namche&nbsp;Bazaar&nbsp;or&nbsp;Manang,&nbsp;we&nbsp;take&nbsp;you&nbsp;on&nbsp;a&nbsp;short&nbsp;hike&nbsp;to&nbsp;a&nbsp;higher&nbsp;ridge&nbsp;(e.g.,&nbsp;Everest&nbsp;View&nbsp;Hotel)&nbsp;before&nbsp;returning&nbsp;to&nbsp;a&nbsp;lower&nbsp;elevation&nbsp;to&nbsp;sleep.&nbsp;This&nbsp;triggers&nbsp;your&nbsp;body&nbsp;to&nbsp;produce&nbsp;more&nbsp;red&nbsp;blood&nbsp;cells&nbsp;while&nbsp;you&nbsp;rest.</p><h3><strong>Hydration&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Nutrition</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>The&nbsp;4-Liter&nbsp;Goal:</strong>&nbsp;We&nbsp;encourage&nbsp;drinking&nbsp;3–4&nbsp;liters&nbsp;of&nbsp;water&nbsp;daily.&nbsp;Dehydration&nbsp;mimics&nbsp;and&nbsp;worsens&nbsp;AMS.</li><li><strong>Garlic&nbsp;Soup:</strong>&nbsp;A&nbsp;local&nbsp;Himalayan&nbsp;secret&nbsp;we&nbsp;swear&nbsp;by!&nbsp;Garlic&nbsp;is&nbsp;believed&nbsp;to&nbsp;help&nbsp;thin&nbsp;the&nbsp;blood&nbsp;and&nbsp;aid&nbsp;oxygen&nbsp;circulation.</li><li><strong>The&nbsp;&quot;No-Go&quot;&nbsp;List:</strong>&nbsp;No&nbsp;alcohol,&nbsp;no&nbsp;smoking,&nbsp;and&nbsp;no&nbsp;sleeping&nbsp;pills.&nbsp;These&nbsp;suppress&nbsp;your&nbsp;breathing&nbsp;rate—the&nbsp;last&nbsp;thing&nbsp;you&nbsp;want&nbsp;at&nbsp;5,000&nbsp;meters.</li></ul><h2>3.&nbsp;Management:&nbsp;What&nbsp;Happens&nbsp;if&nbsp;You&nbsp;Get&nbsp;Sick?</h2><p>At&nbsp;<strong>Zeo&nbsp;Tourism</strong>,&nbsp;our&nbsp;motto&nbsp;is:&nbsp;<em>&quot;Don&#39;t&nbsp;go&nbsp;up&nbsp;until&nbsp;symptoms&nbsp;go&nbsp;down.&quot;</em></p><ol><li><strong>Stop&nbsp;Immediately:</strong>&nbsp;If&nbsp;you&nbsp;have&nbsp;a&nbsp;headache&nbsp;and&nbsp;nausea,&nbsp;we&nbsp;halt&nbsp;the&nbsp;ascent.&nbsp;You&nbsp;stay&nbsp;at&nbsp;the&nbsp;current&nbsp;altitude&nbsp;for&nbsp;24–48&nbsp;hours.</li><li><strong>Medication&nbsp;(Diamox):</strong>&nbsp;Many&nbsp;of&nbsp;our&nbsp;trekkers&nbsp;use&nbsp;<strong>Acetazolamide&nbsp;(Diamox)</strong>&nbsp;as&nbsp;a&nbsp;preventative.&nbsp;It&nbsp;helps&nbsp;you&nbsp;breathe&nbsp;deeper&nbsp;and&nbsp;faster.&nbsp;<em>Always&nbsp;consult&nbsp;your&nbsp;doctor&nbsp;before&nbsp;your&nbsp;trip.</em></li><li><strong>The&nbsp;Immediate&nbsp;Descent:</strong>&nbsp;If&nbsp;symptoms&nbsp;worsen&nbsp;or&nbsp;signs&nbsp;of&nbsp;HAPE/HACE&nbsp;appear,&nbsp;we&nbsp;begin&nbsp;an&nbsp;immediate&nbsp;descent&nbsp;of&nbsp;at&nbsp;least&nbsp;500–1,000m.</li><li><strong>Oxygen&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Gamow&nbsp;Bags:</strong>&nbsp;On&nbsp;high-pass&nbsp;treks,&nbsp;we&nbsp;carry&nbsp;supplemental&nbsp;oxygen&nbsp;and&nbsp;portable&nbsp;hyperbaric&nbsp;chambers&nbsp;(Gamow&nbsp;bags)&nbsp;to&nbsp;stabilize&nbsp;guests&nbsp;before&nbsp;evacuation.</li></ol><h2>ZEO&nbsp;FAQ:&nbsp;Altitude&nbsp;Sickness&nbsp;in&nbsp;Nepal</h2><h3><strong>Can&nbsp;fitness&nbsp;prevent&nbsp;altitude&nbsp;sickness?</strong></h3><p>No.&nbsp;Interestingly,&nbsp;being&nbsp;&quot;too&nbsp;fit&quot;&nbsp;can&nbsp;sometimes&nbsp;be&nbsp;a&nbsp;risk&nbsp;factor&nbsp;because&nbsp;athletes&nbsp;tend&nbsp;to&nbsp;hike&nbsp;faster&nbsp;than&nbsp;their&nbsp;bodies&nbsp;can&nbsp;acclimatize.&nbsp;AMS&nbsp;doesn&#39;t&nbsp;care&nbsp;about&nbsp;your&nbsp;marathon&nbsp;time—it&nbsp;only&nbsp;cares&nbsp;about&nbsp;your&nbsp;pace&nbsp;of&nbsp;ascent.</p><h3><strong>What&nbsp;does&nbsp;an&nbsp;altitude&nbsp;headache&nbsp;feel&nbsp;like?</strong></h3><p>It&nbsp;is&nbsp;usually&nbsp;a&nbsp;throbbing&nbsp;pain,&nbsp;often&nbsp;felt&nbsp;behind&nbsp;the&nbsp;eyes&nbsp;or&nbsp;at&nbsp;the&nbsp;temples,&nbsp;that&nbsp;gets&nbsp;worse&nbsp;when&nbsp;bending&nbsp;over&nbsp;or&nbsp;lying&nbsp;down.</p><h3><strong>Does&nbsp;travel&nbsp;insurance&nbsp;cover&nbsp;altitude&nbsp;sickness?</strong></h3><p>Most&nbsp;standard&nbsp;plans&nbsp;do&nbsp;not.&nbsp;We&nbsp;require&nbsp;all&nbsp;our&nbsp;guests&nbsp;to&nbsp;have&nbsp;specific&nbsp;<strong>High-Altitude&nbsp;Trekking&nbsp;Insurance</strong>&nbsp;that&nbsp;covers&nbsp;helicopter&nbsp;evacuation&nbsp;up&nbsp;to&nbsp;6,000m.</p><h2>Trek&nbsp;Safely&nbsp;with&nbsp;Zeo&nbsp;Tourism</h2><p>We&nbsp;believe&nbsp;the&nbsp;mountains&nbsp;should&nbsp;be&nbsp;enjoyed,&nbsp;not&nbsp;&quot;conquered&quot;&nbsp;at&nbsp;the&nbsp;expense&nbsp;of&nbsp;your&nbsp;health.&nbsp;Our&nbsp;itineraries&nbsp;are&nbsp;designed&nbsp;by&nbsp;experts&nbsp;who&nbsp;live&nbsp;and&nbsp;breathe&nbsp;the&nbsp;Himalayas.</p>','https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1551632811-561732d1e306?q=80&w=2070','Dr. Ang Dorje','Health & Safety',NULL,'7 min read',1,'published',NULL,'2024-02-27 18:15:00','2026-07-05 19:19:00','2025-12-20 13:49:30');
